ZCZC GE07
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 172300 UTC
MONDAY EVENING HIGH PRESSURE 1025 IS EXP TO BE CENTRED JUST S OF IRELAND
WITH A DEEP LOW PRESSURE 982 CENTRED OVER FINLAND GRADUALLY FLN AS IT
MOVS EWARDS. HIGH PRESSURE IS EXP TO MOV STEADILY E TO BECOME CENTRED OVER
SERN PARTS OF THE UK ON TUESDAY AND WEDNESDAY. MEANWHILE A COMPLEXITY OF
LOW PRESSURE SYSTEMS WILL BE SITUATED TO THE SW AND NW OF THE UK DURING THE
REMAINDER OF THE PERIOD WITH ASSOCIATED FRONTAL SYSTEM EXP TO MOV INTO NWERN
PARTS OF THE UK DURING WEDNESDAY AND THURSDAY. STRG WINDS ARE LIKELY TO AFFECT
NERN PARTS OF CULLERCOATS DURING MONDAY EVENING WITH THE RISK OF NEAR GALES
BEFORE WINDS EASE ON TUESDAY. THERE IS THE CHANCE OF FURTHER STRG WINDS AFFECTING
NERN CULLERCOATS AREAS FM LATE WEDNESDAY PERHAPS NEAR GALES ACROSS N UTSIRE
AND S UTSIRE ON THURSDAY. GENERALLY NO FURTHER HAZARDOUS WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS
CULLERCOATS SEA AREAS DURING THE REMAINDER OF THE FCST PERIOD
